!!!
%html
  %head
    %title Attendance Lottery
    %link{:rel => :stylesheet, :href => '/lottery/css/styles.css', :type => 'text/css'}
    %script{:src => '/lottery/javascripts/jquery.min.js'}
    %script{:src => '/lottery/javascripts/soundmanager2-nodebug.js'}
    %script{:src => '/lottery/javascripts/app.js'}
  %body
    #header
      %a{:href => "/lottery"} 
        %h1 Attendance Lottery
    #content
      .aligner
        .demo
          %a{:href => "/lottery/demo"} Working Demo
        .instructions
          %h2 Instructions
          %ol
            %li Run a report on bromcom called Attendance History for last week.
            %li Select all cells and select "Format Cells" from the format menu.
            %li Go to "Allignment" and unselect "merge cells" and "???"
            %li Sort by attendance%
            %li Delete all students that we arent interested in (Students not in your group or not 100% attendance)
            %li Delete every other column than <b>First Name</b>, <b>Last Name</b> and <b>Form Group</b>
            %li File -> Save As. Select <b>CSV</b> from format type.
            %li Upload here.
        
        %form{:action => "/lottery/lottery", :method => :post, :enctype => "multipart/form-data"}
          %label File:
          %input{:type => :file, :name => :file, :id => :file}
          %br
          %input{:type => :submit, :name => :subit, :value => "Generate Lottery"}

      
      #footer 
        %p &copy; George Drummond 2011. All Rights Reserved.
        %p Look at the code on <a href="http://github.com/georgedrummond/attendance_lottery">GitHub</a>, its open source.
